# Copy this file to `.env` in the project root and set your Web client ID.
# Vite does NOT load `.env.example` — only `.env` / `.env.local`.
# Restart the dev server after changing `.env`.
#
# Google Cloud → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client IDs → *Web application* (not Desktop).
# Authorized JavaScript origins — add each exact origin (scheme + host + port):
#   • http://localhost:5181   (or your Vite dev port)
#   • http://127.0.0.1:53463  (installed app; 127.0.0.1 and localhost are different to Google)
# If you see "Error 400: redirect_uri_mismatch", you are missing the origin above or used
# the wrong client type. Optionally add Authorized redirect URIs:
#   • http://127.0.0.1:53463/
# Optional: change Electron port (must match Google Cloud):
# NOTE_APP_OAUTH_PORT=53463
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
